00:40:55.640 --> 00:40:59.450
As I told you, I am very
interested in early music,

00:40:59.450 --> 00:41:01.400
and of course in
contemporary music.

00:41:01.400 --> 00:41:07.580
And I found one
interesting French medieval

00:41:07.580 --> 00:41:11.420
Gesamtkunstwerk,
actually, the first one

00:41:11.420 --> 00:41:14.950
in history, "Roman de Fauvel."

00:41:14.950 --> 00:41:19.910
The story is about a very
ambitious ass, horse,

00:41:19.910 --> 00:41:25.700
who was very greedy, and has
all these terrible, terrible

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:28.160
characteristics--

00:41:28.160 --> 00:41:33.530
egotism, hedonism, hypocrisy,
and all this kind of sin,

00:41:33.530 --> 00:41:35.210
and corruption.

00:41:35.210 --> 00:41:40.730
And this-- Fauvel is his name--

00:41:40.730 --> 00:41:47.180
was the piece which was staged
in Basel opera, Basel Theater.

00:41:47.180 --> 00:41:51.600
And it was kind of
transparent curtain

00:41:51.600 --> 00:41:57.900
behind listeners can follow
events from this 14th century.

00:41:57.900 --> 00:42:01.920
But I think everybody
was aware that it was not

00:42:01.920 --> 00:42:04.860
the right time of the action.

00:42:04.860 --> 00:42:07.770
Because this Fauvel
was serving kind

00:42:07.770 --> 00:42:13.470
of as a metaphor for
actual political happening

00:42:13.470 --> 00:42:17.150
across Atlantic, from
European perspective.

00:42:17.150 --> 00:42:18.243
"Fauvel."

00:42:18.243 --> 00:42:21.141
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

